                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.21/11–1349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 14, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>457. Re Army tel cite C 53512, Nov 13,<note n="48" xml:id="d457fn48">Not printed;
                        it requested diplomatic clearance for a staff team from Far East Air Force
                        to visit Taipei (811.2394A/11–1349).</note> passed to Taipei by Dept.
                    Understand Dept Army sending interim message to SCAP advising that trip be
                    postponed pending further consideration Washington. Will keep you advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
